# Cloudflare Pages redirect rules — https://developers.cloudflare.com/pages/configuration/redirects/
#
# This CF Pages project serves ONLY https://solfege-pro.pages.dev/ (the
# canonical https://solfegepro.com/ is GitHub Pages + Fastly, a separate
# origin), so a blanket path rule below cannot loop: it fires only for
# traffic that lands on the stale pages.dev host and 301s it to the
# canonical domain, preserving the path.
#
# NOTE: CF Pages does NOT support hostnames in the source field (that is
# Netlify syntax) — source must be a path starting with "/".
/*  https://solfegepro.com/:splat  301
